<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="89" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,626,1337]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,284,626,652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Description:</emphasis>
—Thallus corticolous, up to 
<quantity box="[609,665,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
in diam., tightly attached to the substrate, firm, or sometimes flaking off, minutely felty, dull, white to grey, with many calcium oxalate crystals. Hypothallus byssoid, white, composed of 1–2 µm wide hyphae. Prothallus up to 
<quantity box="[605,670,698,725]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
wide, white, byssoid, composed of interwoven and radiating hyphae. Pseudisidia numerous, of the same colour as the thallus, globular, up to 0.1 × 
<quantity box="[1000,1089,734,761]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
. Photobiont 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1817" box="[1229,1371,734,760]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Trentepohliaceae" genus="Trentepohlia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Trentepohliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1229,1371,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Trentepohlia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, single or a few cells aggregated, cells globose, 5–10 × 4–8 µm, yellowish green. Asci and pycnidia not seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,626,1337]" box="[189,1452,806,833]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,325,806,832]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Chemistry:</emphasis>
—Thallus K–, C+ bright red, P–, I– medulla. TLC: gyrophoric acid, lecanoric acid, umbilicaric acid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1003,842,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,626,1337]" box="[189,1003,842,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,842,868]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The epithet “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. F. Chen &amp; L. L. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[502,650,842,868]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="subglobosum">
<emphasis box="[502,650,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">subglobosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to globular pseudisidia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="89" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,626,1337]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,492,878,904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Ecology and distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. F. Chen &amp; L. L. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[527,836,878,904]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="subglobosum">
<emphasis box="[527,836,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Herpothallon subglobosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found growing on bark of trees in a subtropical forest of 
<collectingRegion box="[236,432,914,941]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,626,1337]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,245,950,976]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Note</emphasis>
—This species is characterized by a tightly attached thallus, small globular pseudisidia and the presence of gyrophoric acid, lecanoric acid, umbilicaric acid. Other 
<taxonomicName box="[778,1020,986,1012]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[778,929,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Herpothallon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with pseudisidia and gyrophoric acid include 
<taxonomicName authority="Aptroot &amp; Lucking (2009: 40)" authorityName="Aptroot &amp; Lucking" authorityPageNumber="40" authorityYear="2009" box="[226,678,1022,1048]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fertile">
<emphasis box="[226,328,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. fertile</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Aptroot, A. &amp; Thor, G. &amp; Lucking, R. &amp; Elix, J. A. &amp; Chaves, J. L." box="[333,678,1022,1048]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" pagination="19 - 66" refId="ref3477" refString="Aptroot, A., Thor, G., Lucking, R., Elix, J. A. &amp; Chaves, J. L. (2009) The lichen genus Herpothallon reinstated. Bibliotheca Lichenologica 99: 19 - 66. [http: // www. nhm 2. uio. no / botanisk / lav / RLL / PDF / R 30504. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2009">Aptroot &amp; Lücking (2009: 40)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha (2009: 40)" authorityName="Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha" authorityPageNumber="40" authorityYear="2009" box="[690,1286,1022,1049]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="himalayanum">
<emphasis box="[690,877,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. himalayanum</emphasis>
Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha (2009: 40)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zahlbr.) G. Thor (2009: 44)" authorityName="G. Thor" authorityPageNumber="44" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Zahlbr." class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="japonicum">
<emphasis box="[1298,1451,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. japonicum</emphasis>
(Zahlbr.) G. Thor (2009: 44)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Jagadeesh Ram (2014: 45)" authorityName="Jagadeesh Ram" authorityPageNumber="45" authorityYear="2014" box="[471,914,1058,1085]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="minutum">
<emphasis box="[471,604,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. minutum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M." box="[611,914,1058,1085]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" pagination="39 - 49" refId="ref3995" refString="Jagadeesh Ram, T. A. M., (2014) The genus Herpothallon (Arthoniaceae) in the Andaman Islands, India. The Lichenologist 46 (1): 39 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0024282913000571" type="journal article" year="2014">Jagadeesh Ram (2014: 45)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Vain.) Aptroot &amp; Lucking (2009: 56)" authorityName="Aptroot &amp; Lucking" authorityPageNumber="56" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Vain." class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="philippinum">
<emphasis box="[973,1143,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. philippinum</emphasis>
(Vain.) 
<bibRefCitation author="Aptroot, A. &amp; Thor, G. &amp; Lucking, R. &amp; Elix, J. A. &amp; Chaves, J. L." pageId="6" pageNumber="89" pagination="19 - 66" refId="ref3477" refString="Aptroot, A., Thor, G., Lucking, R., Elix, J. A. &amp; Chaves, J. L. (2009) The lichen genus Herpothallon reinstated. Bibliotheca Lichenologica 99: 19 - 66. [http: // www. nhm 2. uio. no / botanisk / lav / RLL / PDF / R 30504. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2009">Aptroot &amp; Lücking (2009:56)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aptroot &amp; Lucking" authorityYear="2009" box="[262,484,1094,1120]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fertile">
<emphasis box="[262,484,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Herpothallon fertile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a 
<taxonomicName box="[528,764,1094,1120]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[528,679,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">Herpothallon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with asci and ascospores. Other characteristics also distinguish the new species from the non-fertile ones: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jagadeesh Ram &amp; Sinha" authorityYear="2009" box="[615,801,1130,1156]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="himalayanum">
<emphasis box="[615,801,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. himalayanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a loosely appressed thallus, with a hypothallus that is mostly lemon yellow and the species has larger pseudisidia (up to 1 × 
<quantity box="[940,1031,1166,1193]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
); 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Thor" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Zahlbr." box="[1052,1206,1167,1192]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="japonicum">
<emphasis box="[1052,1206,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. japonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a more distinctly C+ red thallus (gyrophoric acid, ovoic acid, lecanoric acid and 2-O-methyllecanoric acid), cylindrical pseudisidia (up to 0.7 × 
<quantity box="[232,320,1238,1265]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
) and its thalli lack calcium oxalate (
<bibRefCitation author="Aptroot, A. &amp; Thor, G. &amp; Lucking, R. &amp; Elix, J. A. &amp; Chaves, J. L." box="[730,953,1238,1264]" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" pagination="19 - 66" refId="ref3477" refString="Aptroot, A., Thor, G., Lucking, R., Elix, J. A. &amp; Chaves, J. L. (2009) The lichen genus Herpothallon reinstated. Bibliotheca Lichenologica 99: 19 - 66. [http: // www. nhm 2. uio. no / botanisk / lav / RLL / PDF / R 30504. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2009">
Aptroot 
<emphasis box="[827,884,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jagadeesh Ram" authorityYear="2014" box="[973,1106,1239,1264]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Herpothallon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="minutum">
<emphasis box="[973,1106,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="89">H. minutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a greenish grey to greyish yellow thallus and dense, minute, granular globular to short cylindrical 
<quantity box="[957,1122,1274,1301]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="89" unit="mm" value="0.04" valueMax="0.06" valueMin="0.02">0.02–0.06 mm</quantity>
wide pseudisidia (
